description: This episode of the series “Louisiana Legends” from December 16, 1983, features an interview with Al Hirt conducted by Gus Weill. Hirt, a native of New Orleans, is a world renowned jazz trumpeter. He discusses: his early interest in trumpeting; his education in classical music and his growing interest in jazz; his friendships with Louis Armstrong, Frank Sinatra, and Pete Fountain; and his discovery by a record company. He also performs “September Song.”
